The true version (as Cobet was the first to point out in his Collectanea Critim p. 431 ff.) is doubtless that given in lamblichus (life of Pythagoras c. 33 ἓ 234 sq. ed. Kiessling) from Aristoxenum, who heard the story srom Dionysius himself.

From this account it appears that the whole proceeding was devised as a joke for the purpose of testing the constancy of Phintias and Damon’s friendship.
